title: How has the proportion of category A (red 1 and 2) calls attended within 8 minutes varied by commissioning region?
analysis_commentary: The proportion of category A calls attended within eight minutes varies at the regional level in a similar manner to the national level, although London has a tendency to more extreme peaks and troughs. There have only been three occasions since April 2014 where an area has achieved the target of attending 75% of Category A calls within eight minutes. London's performance encountered a particularly challenging period since April 2014, going below 50% in December 2014.
